channel.title: Couples Therapy with Candice and Casey
channel.description: You're used to seeing Casey Neistat share his own life through his popular YouTube video series. But now, listen to Casey and his wife Candice discuss candidly the ups and downs of their marriage, friendship, parenting, and lives in the YouTube spotlight.

item.title: Rules of war
item.description: Casey understands emotional issues better when Candice makes analogies to war. Seems healthy? Plus, you simply cannot have friends of the opposite sex once you’re married. Don’t be mad at the truth.
item.dc:creator: Casey Neistat and Candice Pool

item.title: Is it too late now to say sorry?
item.description: There’s no limit to giving an apology. Also, should candice start a YouTube channel?

item.title: He said I looked like a teletubby
item.description: Short but funny! Casey calls Candice a Teletubby and, oddly, she thinks it's hilarious. Throw in stories about supporting your partner in little ways and supporting yourself while being an entrepreneur. Q & A's back again!

item.title: How far do you take it?
item.description: Fake passwords, divorce, drugging toddlers, and fancy watches. Plus Q&A is back!

item.title: Let's Try This Again
item.description: Getting back into the swing of things with some good name calling and guilt trips for taking time alone.
item.dc:creator: Casey Neistat and Candice Pool
item.itunes:summary: Getting back into the swing of things with some good name calling and guilt trips for taking time alone.

item.title: We're back, baby! With a baby!
item.description: The Neistats discuss nudity and hot dogs. Not at the same time.
item.dc:creator: Casey Neistat and Candice Pool
item.itunes:summary: The Neistats discuss nudity and hot dogs. Not at the same time.

item.title: It wasn't always like this
item.description: Everyone goes up, everyone’s needs evolve. Timing is everything. Plus some pregnancy talk—deal with it, it’s almost over.
item.dc:creator: Casey Neistat and Candice Pool
item.itunes:summary: Everyone goes up, everyone’s needs evolve. Timing is everything. Plus some pregnancy talk—deal with it, it’s almost over.

item.title: Peel That Onion
item.description: Think you’re fighting about dirty dishes? How ‘bout save some time and dig deeper. Once you remove a few layers, It’s never about the dishes.
item.dc:creator: Casey Neistat and Candice Pool
item.itunes:summary: Think you’re fighting about dirty dishes? How ‘bout save some time and dig deeper. Once you remove a few layers, It’s never about the dishes.

item.title: 40 Year Old Still Listens to Mom
item.description: Candice unapologetically still leans on her parents to be her... parents. Casey counters how he became his own parent as a runaway teen. Plus some pretty sloppy advice during questions and answers.
item.dc:creator: Casey Neistat and Candice Pool

item.title: Obligation Station
item.description: Casey tries to do what's right for family and fans, but Candice pushes him to balance that with what's right for him right now. And lots of other stuff.
item.dc:creator: Casey Neistat and Candice Pool
item.itunes:summary: Casey tries to do what's right for family and fans, but Candice pushes him to balance that with what's right for him right now. And lots of other stuff.

item.title: This Time, Casey Might Be Right
item.description: The dividing line between truly upset and truly hormonal is starting to get blurred. Casey is doing his best to keep the last months of pregnancy pleasant for all involved — including using Dr. P as a mediator to get through to Candice.
item.dc:creator: Casey Neistat and Candice Pool

item.title: Be Forgiving
item.description: Candice encourages Casey to be kinder to himself today about tough situations in the past; if only she could get a word in through all the giggles.
item.dc:creator: Casey Neistat and Candice Pool

item.title: He'll Never Slow Down
item.description: Candice brings Casey and his dreams of a slower paced life back to reality. Workaholics don't change, and that doesn't have to be a bad thing.
item.dc:creator: Casey Neistat and Candice Pool

item.title: I’m Not Screaming, You’re Screaming
item.description: Candice and Casey may disagree on big things like parenting and where to live, but they have found the perfect sleeping arrangement. So there’s that.

item.title: Low Expectations
item.description: Candice and casey examine their difference in expectations and discover it's best to not have any.

item.title: Long Distance Drama
item.description: Candice and Casey discuss how traveling for work affects a relationship.

item.itunes:summary: Candice and Casey discuss how traveling for work affects a relationship.

item.title: Invading Spaces
item.description: Candice and Casey discuss the right way to invade someone’s personal space, and what happens to your independence when you commit to a relationship.

item.title: Don't Touch Me
item.description:
Candice and Casey discuss affection and openness and realize that they have more in common than they thought.
